Package: popgenVCF
Type: Package
Title: Population Genomics Toolkit for VCF Data
Version: 0.10.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Marc-Olivier", family = "Duceppe",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "marc-olivier.duceppe@inspection.gc.ca",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2130-0427"))
    )
Author: Marc-Olivier Duceppe [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Marc-Olivier Duceppe <marc-olivier.duceppe@inspection.gc.ca>
Description: A modular command-line toolkit and R application programming
    interface for reproducible population-genomic analysis of diploid,
    biallelic single-nucleotide polymorphism data stored in Variant Call
    Format (VCF) files. The toolkit performs sample and variant quality control,
    fixed-parameter linkage-disequilibrium pruning with 'SNPRelate', genetic
    diversity summaries, principal component analysis, identity-by-state
    analyses, neighbour-joining trees, Weir-Cockerham FST, discriminant analysis
    of principal components, analysis of molecular variance, Mantel tests,
    isolation-by-distance analysis, external 'ADMIXTURE' cross-validation,
    chromosome-specific analyses, chromosome-block bootstrap confidence
    intervals, manuscript-oriented reporting, and deterministic execution with
    dependency-aware failure propagation, checkpoints, bounded retries, and
    elapsed-time budgets.
